# Schema: Polkadot SDK PRDoc Schema (prdoc) v1.0.0
# See doc at https://raw.githubusercontent.com/paritytech/polkadot-sdk/master/prdoc/schema_user.json

title: Add `create_with_id` to pallet-nfts

doc:
  - audience: Runtime Dev
    description: |
      Adds a `create_with_id` extrinsic to `pallet-nfts` that creates a collection
      at a caller-specified `CollectionId` instead of the auto-incrementing
      counter, e.g. for a 1:1 mapping between a DAO and its collection.

      ```rust
      pub fn create_with_id(
          origin: OriginFor<T>,
          collection: T::CollectionId,
          admin: AccountIdLookupOf<T>,
          config: CollectionConfigFor<T, I>,
      ) -> DispatchResult
      ```

      Gated by a new `CreateWithIdOrigin`, separate from `CreateOrigin` so that
      picking an explicit ID can be restricted independently. Fails with
      `CollectionIdInUse` if the ID is taken and `WrongSetting` if
      `DepositRequired` is disabled in the config.

      Breaking: `pallet_nfts::Config` gains two required items:

      - `CreateWithIdOrigin: EnsureOriginWithArg<RuntimeOrigin, CollectionId,
        Success = AccountId>` gates `create_with_id`. The provided runtimes leave
        it unrestricted (equal to `CreateOrigin`); the `Config` item documents how
        to restrict it (a member set, or an ID-range check on the `CollectionId`
        arg) so callers cannot take IDs they could not reach via `create()`.
      - `NextId: NextCollectionIdProvider` is the sole source of collection IDs;
        `create()` and `force_create()` no longer access `NextCollectionId`
        directly. Two implementations are provided: `IncrementalNextId<T, I>`
        reads and increments `NextCollectionId` (existing behaviour), and
        `DisabledNextId<T, I>` makes `create()`/`force_create()` fail with
        `Error::MethodDisabled` for runtimes that only use `create_with_id()`.

      `create_with_id` calls `claim(id)` on the provider. With
      `IncrementalNextId`, claiming an ID at or above the counter (or with the
      counter unset) sets the counter to `id.increment()` so later `create()`
      calls cannot collide. Lower IDs leave the counter unchanged. Custom
      providers can track used IDs via `next()` and `claim(id)`.

      `NextCollectionIdIncremented` is now emitted when an ID is allocated,
      before `Created`/`ForceCreated`, and from `create_with_id` when the claim
      moves the counter.

      The `Create` trait method `create_collection_with_id` now also calls
      `claim(id)`, so callers no longer risk claiming a value in the ID sequence.

